<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <title>KeepUp Terms of Service</title>
    <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.0/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/assets/css/main.css" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/assets/css/legal-page.css" />
  </head>
  <body class="no-nav bg-light legal-page">
    <main class="container py-5">
      <section class="legal-shell mx-auto">
        <div class="card shadow-sm border-0 legal-hero mb-4">
          <div class="card-body p-4 p-md-5">
            <p class="legal-kicker mb-2">KeepUp CRM</p>
            <h1 class="display-6 mb-3">Terms of Service</h1>
            <p class="lead text-secondary mb-3">
              These Terms of Service govern access to and use of the KeepUp CRM platform by builders,
              sales teams, and their authorized users.
            </p>
            <p class="legal-updated mb-0">
              <strong>Last Updated:</strong> <%= lastUpdated %>
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="card shadow-sm border-0">
          <div class="card-body p-4 p-md-5">
            <div class="legal-copy">
              <section class="legal-section" aria-labelledby="overview">
                <h2 id="overview">Overview</h2>
                <p>
                  KeepUp provides a business software platform designed for home builders, sales teams,
                  and related internal users to manage contacts, workflows, sales activity, communications,
                  reporting, and related operational data. By accessing or using KeepUp, you agree to these
                  Terms of Service on behalf of yourself and, if applicable, the company or organization you
                  represent.
                </p>
                <p>
                  If you do not agree to these terms, do not access or use the platform.
                </p>
              </section>

              <section class="legal-section" aria-labelledby="eligibility">
                <h2 id="eligibility">Eligibility and Accounts</h2>
                <p>
                  KeepUp is intended for business use. You must be authorized by your employer or business
                  organization to create an account or use the platform. You are responsible for maintaining
                  the confidentiality of your login credentials and for all activity that occurs under your account.
                </p>
                <p>
                  You agree to provide accurate account information and to update it as needed so it remains current.
                  We may refuse, limit, or revoke access if account information is inaccurate, misleading, or unauthorized.
                </p>
              </section>

              <section class="legal-section" aria-labelledby="platform-use">
                <h2 id="platform-use">Use of the Platform</h2>
                <p>
                  Subject to these terms, KeepUp grants you a limited, non-exclusive, non-transferable,
                  revocable right to access and use the platform for your internal business purposes.
                </p>
                <p>
                  You may use KeepUp only in compliance with applicable laws, regulations, and industry requirements,
                  including those related to privacy, marketing, electronic communications, and data security.
                </p>
              </section>

              <section class="legal-section" aria-labelledby="customer-data">
                <h2 id="customer-data">Customer Data and User Responsibility</h2>
                <p>
                  You are responsible for the accuracy, quality, legality, and appropriateness of all data,
                  files, messages, contact records, notes, and other content that you or your users upload,
                  store, send, or otherwise enter into KeepUp.
                </p>
                <p>
                  You represent that you have all rights, permissions, and legal bases needed to use that data
                  with the platform. KeepUp does not verify customer-entered data for accuracy or legal compliance
                  and is not responsible for errors, omissions, or unlawful content provided by users.
                </p>
              </section>

              <section class="legal-section" aria-labelledby="communications">
                <h2 id="communications">Email and Communications Compliance</h2>
                <p>
                  If you use KeepUp to send emails, campaigns, notifications, or other communications, you are
                  solely responsible for obtaining any required consent and for complying with all applicable laws,
                  regulations, and messaging rules. This includes rules related to opt-in requirements, opt-out
                  requests, sender identification, suppression handling, and truthful message content.
                </p>
                <p>
                  Misuse of communication tools, including spam, misleading content, unauthorized outreach, or
                  sending to recipients without appropriate consent, is prohibited and may result in immediate
                  suspension or termination of access.
                </p>
              </section>

              <section class="legal-section" aria-labelledby="availability">
                <h2 id="availability">Service Availability and No Warranty</h2>
                <p>
                  KeepUp may update, modify, suspend, or discontinue any part of the platform at any time.
                  The platform is provided on an &ldquo;as is&rdquo; and &ldquo;as available&rdquo; basis.
                </p>
                <p>
                  KeepUp does not guarantee uninterrupted availability, error-free operation, or any specific uptime,
                  response time, delivery rate, or performance level. To the maximum extent permitted by law,
                  KeepUp disclaims all warranties, express or implied, including implied warranties of merchantability,
                  fitness for a particular purpose, and non-infringement.
                </p>
              </section>

              <section class="legal-section" aria-labelledby="fees">
                <h2 id="fees">Fees and Billing</h2>
                <p>
                  Access to some KeepUp features or service levels may require payment under a separate order,
                  subscription, invoice, or billing arrangement. Unless otherwise agreed in writing, fees are due
                  as billed and are non-refundable except where required by law.
                </p>
                <p>
                  We may suspend access for overdue amounts or billing-related issues after reasonable notice where appropriate.
                </p>
              </section>

              <section class="legal-section" aria-labelledby="ip">
                <h2 id="ip">Intellectual Property</h2>
                <p>
                  KeepUp and its related software, interface designs, workflows, trademarks, branding, and related
                  materials are owned by KeepUp or its licensors and are protected by applicable intellectual property laws.
                </p>
                <p>
                  Except for the limited use rights expressly granted in these terms, no ownership rights or licenses
                  are transferred to you.
                </p>
              </section>

              <section class="legal-section" aria-labelledby="acceptable-use">
                <h2 id="acceptable-use">Acceptable Use / Prohibited Conduct</h2>
                <p>You may not use KeepUp to:</p>
                <ul>
                  <li>violate any law, regulation, or third-party right;</li>
                  <li>upload or distribute unlawful, infringing, deceptive, or harmful content;</li>
                  <li>send spam, unauthorized marketing, or misleading communications;</li>
                  <li>interfere with the platform, attempt unauthorized access, or bypass security measures;</li>
                  <li>reverse engineer, scrape, or misuse the service beyond authorized business use; or</li>
                  <li>use the platform in a way that could harm KeepUp, its systems, or other users.</li>
                </ul>
              </section>

              <section class="legal-section" aria-labelledby="termination">
                <h2 id="termination">Suspension and Termination</h2>
                <p>
                  KeepUp may suspend, restrict, or terminate access to the platform at any time if we believe there has
                  been misuse, a security issue, nonpayment, unlawful activity, or a violation of these terms. This includes
                  misuse of email or communication tools.
                </p>
                <p>
                  You may stop using the platform at any time. Upon termination, your right to use the platform ends immediately,
                  but provisions that by their nature should survive termination will remain in effect.
                </p>
              </section>

              <section class="legal-section" aria-labelledby="liability">
                <h2 id="liability">Limitation of Liability</h2>
                <p>
                  To the maximum extent permitted by law, KeepUp will not be liable for any indirect, incidental, special,
                  consequential, exemplary, or punitive damages, or for any loss of profits, revenue, goodwill, data, or business
                  opportunities arising out of or related to the use of, or inability to use, the platform.
                </p>
                <p>
                  To the maximum extent permitted by law, KeepUp&rsquo;s total liability for any claim relating to the platform
                  will not exceed the amount paid by the customer to KeepUp for the applicable service during the twelve months
                  preceding the event giving rise to the claim.
                </p>
              </section>

              <section class="legal-section" aria-labelledby="indemnification">
                <h2 id="indemnification">Indemnification</h2>
                <p>
                  You agree to defend, indemnify, and hold harmless KeepUp and its affiliates, officers, employees, and agents
                  from and against claims, damages, losses, liabilities, costs, and expenses arising out of or related to your
                  data, your use of the platform, your communications sent through the platform, or your violation of these terms
                  or applicable law.
                </p>
              </section>

              <section class="legal-section" aria-labelledby="changes">
                <h2 id="changes">Changes to the Services or Terms</h2>
                <p>
                  KeepUp may update these terms from time to time. Updated terms become effective when posted to this page or
                  otherwise communicated to you, unless a later effective date is stated. Your continued use of the platform after
                  the effective date of updated terms constitutes acceptance of the revised terms.
                </p>
                <p>
                  We may also change, add, or remove features from the platform at any time.
                </p>
              </section>

              <section class="legal-section" aria-labelledby="governing-law">
                <h2 id="governing-law">Governing Law</h2>
                <p>
                  These terms are governed by the laws identified in the applicable order form or other written agreement
                  between KeepUp and the customer. If no separate written agreement specifies governing law, then the laws of
                  the jurisdiction where the applicable KeepUp contracting entity is organized will govern, without regard to
                  conflict of law principles.
                </p>
              </section>

              <section class="legal-section" aria-labelledby="contact">
                <h2 id="contact">Contact Information</h2>
                <p>
                  Questions about these Terms of Service may be sent to
                  <a href="mailto:<%= supportEmail %>"><%= supportEmail %></a>.
                </p>
              </section>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
    </main>
  </body>
</html>
